{"title_page": "Shireen Akhter", "text_new": "{{infobox officeholder\n| name        = Shireen Akhter \n| office       = 18th Vice Chancellor of the [[University of Chittagong]]\n| term_start = 3 November 2019\n| predecessor = [[Iftekhar Uddin Chowdhury]]\n| occupation  = university academic \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1956|05|01|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Cox's Bazar]], [[East Pakistan]], Pakistan\n| website = [http://cu.ac.bd/public_profile/index.php?ein=3393 Dr. Shireen Akhter Profile]\n}}\n\n'''Shireen Akhter''' (born 1 May 1956)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/city/news/prof-shireen-made-acting-vc-cu-1756660|title=Prof Shireen made acting VC of CU|date=2019-06-14|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2019-11-04}}</ref> is a Bangladeshi academic and the first female vice chancellor  of the [[University of Chittagong]].<ref name=\"bdnews24\">{{Cite news |url=https://bdnews24.com/bn/detail/ctg/1684665 |title=\u099a\u09ac\u09bf\u09a4\u09c7 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u09a8\u09be\u09b0\u09c0 \u09ad\u09bf\u09b8\u09bf \u09b6\u09bf\u09b0\u09c0\u09a3 \u0986\u0996\u09a4\u09be\u09b0 |access-date=3 November 2019 |publisher=bdnews24}}</ref><ref name=\"cu\">{{Cite web |url=http://cu.ac.bd/public_profile/index.php?ein=3393 |title=Dr. Shireen Akhter CU |website=cu.ac.bd |access-date=3 November 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"eisamay\">{{Cite news |url=https://eisamay.indiatimes.com/bangladesh-news/bangladesh-jadavpur-university-alumni-shireen-akhter-appointed-as-next-vc-of-chittagong-university/articleshow/71883498.cms |title=\u099a\u099f\u09cd\u099f\u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09ae \u09ac\u09bf\u09b6\u09cd\u09ac\u09ac\u09bf\u09a6\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09b2\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u0989\u09aa\u09be\u099a\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09af \u09aa\u09a6\u09c7 \u09af\u09be\u09a6\u09ac\u09aa\u09c1\u09b0\u09c7\u09b0 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4\u09a8\u09c0 |access-date=3 November 2019 |publisher=\u098f\u0987\u09b8\u09ae\u09af\u09bc.\u0987\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be \u099f\u09be\u0987\u09ae\u09b8}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2016/03/28/cu-gets-first-female-pro-vc |title=CU gets first female Pro VC |date=2016-03-28 |website=Dhaka Tribune |access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>\nShe started worked as a VC of University of Chittagong on 3 November 2019.<ref name=\"bdnews24\" /> Lone female member of Election Commission (EC) Search committee Akhter joined CU as a lecturer of Bangla department in 1996.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.banglanews24.com/education/article/77336/Prof-Shirin-takes-charge-of-CU-VC |title=Prof Shirin takes charge of CU VC |date=2019-06-13 |website=Banglanews24.com |language=en |access-date=2019-06-14}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nAkhter was born at Eid Gao in [[Cox's Bazar]] on 1 May 1956.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://dailyasianage.com/news/14613/dr-shirin-akter-first-female-pro-vc-of-cu |title=Dr Shirin Akter, first female Pro-VC of CU |website=The Asian Age |language=en |access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref> Her father was Afsar Kamal Chowdhury and mother was Begum Lutfunnahar Kamal. Her husband is Latiful Alam Chowdhury. She is mother of one son and one daughter.\n\n== Education ==\n* 1973, S.S.C Cox's Bazar Government Girl's School  \n* 1975, H.S.C  Chittagong  Government Women's College\n* 1978, B.A (Honours), Bengali language and literature, University of Chittagong\n* 1981: M.A,  Bengali language and literature, University of Chittagong, Chittagong\n* 1991: Ph.D. Jadavpur University, Kolkata, India. Field of Research: Bangladesher Tinjon Oupanyasik Showkat Osman, Waliullah, Abu Ishaq\n\n==Professional career==\nAkhter joined the university as a lecturer of Bangla Department in 1996 after completing her PhD from [[Jadavpur University]] in India. On her appointment, she told [[bdnews24.com]] that she would try to develop |Chittagong University as a \"source of vast knowledge\" in according with the spirit of the Liberation War.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2016/03/28/first-woman-pro-vice-chancellor-at-chittagong-university |title=First woman pro-Vice Chancellor at Chittagong University |last=Bureau |first=Chittagong |last2=bdnews24.com |website=bdnews24.com |access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\n* 2000, ''Chander Omabosha: Aref Ali'r Manash Jatra''  Pandulipi,Department of Bengali, C.U.\n* 2000 \"Nazrul-er Oupanyash' ''Chiro Unnata Shir'' \"\n* 2000 \"Manab Jiboney Nodir Vhumika O Syed  Waliullahar Nodi Tattik Oupannyash' \u201c Kotasahitto\u201d, Kolkata.\n* 2001 \u201cNazrul Oupanyashey Kobi  Vhabna\u201d ''Nazrul Institute Journal'', Dhaka.\n* 2005\u20132006 'Umratul Fazal: Ek Snigdho Dip Shikha',  \u201cSchool of Women Studies Patrika\u201d, Jadavpur University, Kolkata,  .\n* 2005\u20132006, 'Amader Chota Golpey  Ekush-er Chetona' \u201c Kothasahitto\u201d, Mittra & Gosh, Kolkata,  .\n* 2005\u20132006, 'Kolpana Datta Biplobey Vhaibobey' \u201cEkshatey\u201d,  Kolkata,  .\n* 2005\u20132006, 'Chattagramey Mohila Giti Sohela', \u201cEkshatey\u201d  Kolkata Mohila Porishad Patrika, Kolkota, India.\n* 2007, 'Sailabala Goshjayar Oupanyas 'Sheikh Andu',  \u201cPashimbanga Bangla Academy Patrika\u201d, Pashimbanga, India.\n\n== Conferences and seminars ==\n* She took part in the Ekushey Lecture Serics  organised by the Bangla Academy in the following years: 1996, 2005, 2006, 2008, 2009, 2013,1999: Refreshers Course, Kolkata University,  India.\n* She also participated in the discussion of art  and literature program of Bangladesh Radio and Television and took part in  the seminars of  socio- literary and  mass media based programs.\n\n== Research and creative works ==\n\n===Creative books===\n* Chira Unnata Shir -2000\n* Senobia Rabindranath O  Himeneth Ebong   Annayana Bibechona -2004\n* Jugobani O Nazrul \u2013  Nazrul Institute-2006\n* Bangladesher Tinjon  Oupanyasik  Showkat :  Osman, Waliullah, Abu Ishaq. Published by  Bangla Academy, First  edition 1991, 2nd  edition 2010.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://koha.ulab.edu.bd/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=5450&shelfbrowse_itemnumber=12911 |title=Bangladesher Tin Jon Oupanyasik: Showkat Osman, Syed Waliullah o Abu Ishaque |last=Shireen Akhter |date=1993 |publisher=Bangla Academy |isbn=9789840728480 |location=Dhaka |language=Bengali}}</ref>\n* Shiekh Andu-2015\n\n===Short story books===\n* Swati Nakkhatrer Alo-1995\n* Paribrajjya-2004\n* Chotkar Totka Golpo-2004\n* Mothasha Kanna -2013\n* Judhojiban \u2013 Behola  Bangla-2016\n* Rohinga.- Abishkar-2016\n* Lubdhak \u2013Abishkar-2016\n\n== Accolades ==\n{{BLP unsourced section|date=March 2019}}\n* In 1992, she was given Cox's Bazar Samiti award by Cox's Bazar Association.\n* In 2006, Nazrul birth Jubilee celebration committee awarded her Nazrul Padak.\n* In 2015, 'Shandhipana' Art and cultural organization, Chittagong, awarded her Ekushey Padak.\n\n== Member ==\n* Life Member, Bangla Academy, Bangladesh\n* Vice-President of Private Development organisation UTSA-2006-2010 PRANTIK\n* Executive Member, Private Development organisation UTSA-2011-2013 PRANTIK\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Akhter, Shireen}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Cox's Bazar District]]\n[[Category:University of Chittagong faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Chittagong alumni]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi women academics]]\n[[Category:Vice-Chancellors of the University of Chittagong]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox officeholder\n| name        = Shireen Akhter \n| office       = 18th Vice Chancellor of the [[University of Chittagong]]\n| term_start = 3 November 2019\n| predecessor = [[Iftekhar Uddin Chowdhury]]\n| occupation  = university academic \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1956|05|01|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Cox's Bazar]], [[East Pakistan]], Pakistan\n| website = [http://cu.ac.bd/public_profile/index.php?ein=3393 Dr. Shireen Akhter Profile]\n}}\n\n'''Shireen Akhter''' (born 1 May 1